-- FLOW: paragraph flow layout for closed children in poems
-- Tests that closed children in vertical poems flow together on lines
-- instead of each getting their own line.

=== flow packs small items on line | 40
| a b c d e f g h i j k l m n

=== flow stays flat when fits | 30
| a b c d e f g h i j k l m n

=== flow wraps multiple lines narrow | 20
| aa bb cc dd ee ff
  gg hh

=== flow with open forces vertical | 40
| a b c
    | nested1
    | nested2
  d e f

=== large expr stays flat when fits | 40
| a b (mediumFunction x) c d e

=== flow respects indent | 30
= foo | a b c d e f g h

=== single closed before open | 40
| x | nested

=== multiple closed before single open | 40
| a b c d | nested

=== single open then closed | 40
|
    | nested
  a b c
---
|    | nested
  a b c

=== multi-heir edge case | 40
| | nested
  a b c
---
| | nested
  a
  b
  c

=== flow with expressions fits | 40
| (foo 1) (bar 2) (baz 3) (qux 4)

=== all fits flat | 80
| short items here

=== staircase with closed flow | 50
+ foo a b c
      + x1
      + x2
  + y1
  + y2
+ bar p q r
      + z1
  + z2
+ end

=== closed after open staircase | 40
+ x     + nested1
    + nested2
  a b c d e f g

=== heir with flow children | 40
= def1 | a b c d e f g
= def2 | x y z

=== nested poem vertical | 30
| x | a b c d e f g

=== deeply nested vertical | 25
| a | b c d e f | x y z w

=== tight items flow | 30
| foo.bar baz.qux one.two

=== quoted items fits | 40
| "hello" "world" "foo" "bar" "baz"

=== flow wraps at narrow width | 15
| aaa bbb ccc
  ddd eee

=== flow many items narrow | 12
| a b c d e f g h
---
| a b c d e
  f g h

=== vertical alternating groups | 30
| a b c
    | open1
  d e f
    | open2
  g h i

=== flow after long open one per line | 40
| | thisIsAVeryLongNestedPoem x y
  a b c d
---
| | thisIsAVeryLongNestedPoem x y
  a
  b
  c
  d

=== closed only vertical narrow | 18
| alpha beta gamma delta epsilon
---
| alpha beta gamma
  delta epsilon

=== mixed widths fits | 25
| a bb ccc dddd eeeee f

=== mixed widths wraps | 20
| a bb ccc dddd eeeee f
---
| a bb ccc dddd
  eeeee f

---- EXPR CLEAR WITH OPEN -----------------------------------------------
-- When EXPR CLEAR contains OPEN children followed by siblings,
-- newlines must be forced after the OPEN to prevent content merging

=== tricky open then sibling in expr | 40
(    + foo
  bar
,    + foo
  bar
)
